revision.text:
{{Infobox protected area | name = Bear Creek Lake State Park | iucn_category = III | photo = File:Bear Creek Lake (9669510311).jpg | photo_caption = Bear Creek Lake | location = 22 Bear Creek Lake Rd., near Cumberland, VA |map = USA Virginia#USA | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bear Creek Lake State Park | map_width = | coordinates = {{coords|37|31|54|N|78|16|21|W|region:US-VA|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|329|acre|ha|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Bear Creek Lake State Park|url=http://www.dcr.virginia.gov/state-parks/bear-creek-lake#general_information}}</ref> | established = 1940 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Virginia Department of Conservation and Recreation]] {{Infobox NRHP | embed = yes | added = {{dts|2012|10|31}} | refnum = 12000904<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web |url=http://www.nps.gov/history/nr/listings/20121109.htm |title=Weekly list of actions taken on properties: 10/29/12 through 11/2/12 |date=November 9, 2012 |publisher=[[National Park Service]] |accessdate=November 13, 2012}}</ref> | designated_other1 = Virginia Landmarks Register | designated_other1_date = September 18, 2008<ref name=register>{{cite web|title=Virginia Landmarks Register|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/register_counties_cities.htm|publisher=Virginia Department of Historic Resources|accessdate=5 June 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053819/http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/register_counties_cities.htm|archive-date=2013-09-21|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> | designated_other1_number = 024-0034 | designated_other1_num_position = bottom | image=DSC 6850 (5935482674).jpg | caption=The Lakeside Shelter, a contributing structure to the historic district }} }} '''Bear Creek Lake State Park''' is a {{convert|326|acre|adj=on}} [[state park]] located in [[Cumberland, Virginia]], United States. It is a recreational and camping facility that surrounds an artificial {{convert|40|acre|ha|adj=on}} lake situated in the {{convert|16000|acre|ha|adj=on}} [[Cumberland State Forest]].
==History== Bear Creek Lake was built by members of the [[Civilian Conservation Corps]] in 1938 as a project of the Virginia Department of Agriculture through the State Forestry Division. The lake was built using labor from local carpenters, farmers and un-skilled laborers seeking jobs. In addition to the lake, two pavilions, a concession stand and six fireplaces were constructed. In 1940, the area opened as a forestry wayside with boat rentals and swimming. In 1958, the area was given to the Division of State Parks and was operated as a day-use recreation area. In 1962 the division added campgrounds and the area's name was changed to Bear Creek Lake State Park.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bear Creek Lake State Park |url=http://www.virginiaoutdoors.com/parks/details/bear-creek-lake-state-park |website=Virginia Outdoors |publisher=Imperial Multimedia |accessdate=13 April 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331093452/http://www.virginiaoutdoors.com/parks/details/bear-creek-lake-state-park |archivedate=31 March 2016 |df= }}</ref>
==Attractions== The park features a {{convert|40|acre|adj=on}} lake with a boat launch, fishing pier, boat rentals and a swimming beach. Visitors will also find a meeting facility, cabins, camping, picnicking, an archery range and playgrounds. Guests also enjoy the park's nine trails and access to the adjoining {{convert|16000|acre|adj=on}} [[Cumberland State Forest]], including the {{convert|14|mi|adj=on}} Cumberland Multi-use Trail. This trail is available for hiking, biking and horseback riding.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bear Creek Lake State Park|url=http://www.dcr.virginia.gov/state-parks/bear-creek-lake#general_information|website=Virginia State Parks|publisher=Virginia Department of Conservation and Recreation|accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>
