The '''Laratinga Wetlands''', constructed in 1999, is a [[wetlands|wetland]] located in [[Mount Barker, South Australia]]. It is named after the [[Indigenous Australians|Aboriginal]] Peramangk peoples' name for the Mount Barker Creek, "Laratinga". <ref name="dcmtb-page">{{cite web |url=http://www.dcmtbarker.sa.gov.au/laratingawetlands |title=Laratinga Wetlands |author=District Council of Mt Barker |accessdate=28 April 2015}}</ref>

The wetlands occupy an area of {{convert|16.7|ha|abbr=off}}, of which {{convert|10.7|ha|abbr=off}} is underwater.<ref name="dcmtb-page"/>   

